  "What does 'savings rate' mean in a case study budget analysis?": "",
  "The speed at which you fill your emergency fund": "",
  "The percentage of total income that is saved or invested rather than spent": "",
  "The interest rate on a savings account": "",
  "The rate at which prices decrease during a sale": "",
  "The savings rate is a critical metric in budget analysis: savings divided by income, expressed as a percentage. A 12.5% savings rate means $400 saved from $3,200 income. Higher savings rates accelerate wealth building exponentially.": "",
  "What is 'intentional spending'?": "",
  "Spending to intentionally impress others": "",
  "Making conscious, deliberate spending choices aligned with your values and goals rather than spending impulsively": "",
  "Spending as much as possible on things you enjoy": "",
  "Only spending on necessities and never on wants": "",
